{
  "texts": [
    "This result did not support our initial hypothesis, but as we elaborate in the discussion, sampling one metabolite at one time point may not have been sufficient to characterize the relevant phenotype.",
    "Population branch statistics identify differentially expressed genes under selectionMany of the DEGs detected in our transcriptome experiment, both in response to pathogen challenge and between R/S phenotypes, were unique to each population (Fig. 1A).",
    "This suggests that at least some aspect of each population's defense response against P. palmivora is lineage-specific and that resistance versus susceptibility may be mediated by different genes depending on the population.",
    "This supports our original hypothesis that each wild population adapts to its environment, potentially generating a rich source of novel alleles.",
    "To determine the extent to which natural selection has shaped resistance and susceptibility in each population, we used population branch statistics (PBS) to estimate the lineage-specific genetic differentiation associated with resistant genotypes in each population (Fig. 5A) [90]."
  ]
}